==English==

===Etymology===
A reference to the [[ostrich]]'s habit of burying its head when threatened.

===Adjective===
'''[[head]]-[[in]]-[[the]]-[[sand]]'''
#{{idiom}} Exhibiting [[disregard]] or [[denial]] of a [[problem]] or [[threat]].
#:''The head-in-the-sand approach to environmentalism seldom improves matters.''

===Usage note===
Hyphenated when used as an adjective.